## 12. NestJS key implementation notes

**Auth:**
- `POST /auth/login` → returns `{ access_token: string }` (JWT, 24h expiry)
- JWT payload: `{ sub: userId, email, role }`
- `JwtAuthGuard` on all protected routes; `@Roles('admin','underwriter')` decorator + `RolesGuard`

**Factoring endpoints:**
- `POST /invoices` (carrier) — create invoice, compute advance/fee/reserve in integer cents server-side, status=pending
- `GET /invoices` — filtered by role: carriers see own; underwriters/admins see all
- `PATCH /invoices/:id/approve` (underwriter) — set status=approved, record underwriterId, approvedAt
- `PATCH /invoices/:id/reject` (underwriter) — set status=rejected
- `PATCH /invoices/:id/disburse` (underwriter/admin) — set status=disbursed, post ledger entries (advance leg: Debit FACTORING_REC, Credit CASH_BANK), disbursedAt
- `PATCH /invoices/:id/collect` (admin) — set status=collected, post collection ledger entries (Debit CASH_BANK, Credit FACTORING_REC + Fee Revenue + reserve release), collectedAt

**Ledger endpoints:**
- `GET /accounts` — list all accounts with current balanceMinorUnits
- `GET /accounts/:id/entries` — ledger entries for account, sorted by postedAt desc
- `GET /ledger` — recent entries across all accounts (limit 50)

**Money constraint (hard gate):** All amounts in DB, DTOs, and service layer are integer minor units. The only floating point operation anywhere is in `formatMoney()` at display time. Zod schemas on all money fields: `z.number().int().positive()`.

**Real-DB integration tests (`test/factoring.e2e-spec.ts`):**
```typescript
// Use pg directly against the real test DB (TEST_DATABASE_URL or fallback to DATABASE_URL)
// Test 1: create invoice with known face value -> verify advance/fee/reserve calc (integer math)
// Test 2: approve + disburse -> verify 2 ledger entries posted, account balances updated
// These are the "no mocks on money paths" tests the client grades on
```

`test/jest-e2e.json`:
```json
{
  "moduleFileExtensions": ["js","json","ts"],
  "rootDir": ".",
  "testEnvironment": "node",
  "testRegex": ".e2e-spec.ts$",
  "transform": { "^.+\\.(t|j)s$": "ts-jest" },
  "testTimeout": 30000
}
```

Turbo test command: `turbo run test` (from monorepo root) runs both `apps/api test` tasks.

